READ ME: These two lines enable the kanji dictionary pop-up I made. Click on a Kanji to display the window on the card.
You can choose which field to display in the styling section.
You can see the instruction here: https://imgur.com/a/OATxzm0
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------{{/*}}
<script src ="_kanjax_with_koohii v2.js"></script>
<script src ="_jquery.bpopup.min.js"></script>


{{#*}}-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
READ ME: This gives the audio. The button may appear depending on your device preferences. Check the styling part also for that.
I use the Audio_Extra for just one word, and Audio_Sentence for the full sentence. I use the TTS add-on to create audio.
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------{{/*}}
{{#Audio_Extra}}
	<div id="Audio_Extra">
		{{Audio_Extra}}
	</div>		
{{/Audio_Extra}}

{{#Audio_Sentence}}
	<div id="Audio_Sentence">
		{{Audio_Sentence}}
	</div>
{{/Audio_Sentence}}


{{#*}}-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
READ ME: This display the focus Morph from Morphman. You can change the name but make sure it matches your morphman preferences.
You can see the instruction here: https://imgur.com/a/V9v0Ife
If you don't use Morphman, it won't show up on your card.

The grey background for definition show up if you have a Morph. If you have the edit add-on you can add the type or edit the definition in there.
If you don't want it you can delete the 3 lines, or add hidden to visibility, or change the color in the styling section.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------{{/*}}
{{^Morph}}
<br>	<br>	<br>	
{{/Morph}}

{{#Morph}}
	<div class="Morph">
		{{Morph}}
	</div>
	<div style='visibility: ;'>
		<div class="Definition">
			{{edit:Definition}}
		</div>
	</div>
{{/Morph}}


{{#*}}-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
READ ME: This displays the japanese sentence.
Span class field colorize the target word / morph within the sentence. 
You can see the script for the span class at the bottom. It may conflict with other colorizing add-ons you have.

In front of reading, you can replace "furigana" by "kanji" or "kana" depending on your preferences.
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------{{/*}}
<div class="Reading">
	<span class="field">
		{{furigana:Reading}}
	</span>
</div>


{{#*}}-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
READ ME: This displays the english translation of the sentence, if there is one.
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------{{/*}}
{{#English}}
	<div class="English">
		{{English}}
	</div>
{{/English}}


{{#*}}-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
READ ME:This script replace what's inside the target field with something else.
In my case, it replaces it with the same content but in bold and colorized. I use it to see colorize the target word in the Expression / Reading fields.
It may interfere with Migaku or something else, so you can delete it. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------{{/*}}
<script>
fields = document.querySelectorAll('.field');
for (var i = 0; i < fields.length; i++) {
fields[i].innerHTML = fields[i].innerHTML
.replace('{{Morph}}', '<span style="color: #d48872; font-weight: bold; ">{{Morph}}</span>')}
</script>


{{#*}}-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
READ ME: This creates 2 columns.
The screenshot / snapshot is on the left. Ichie.moe automatic parsing on the right.
You can modify the size of the picture in the styling part.

If there's no screenshot, then it just displays ichie.moe full width.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------{{/*}}
<br>

{{#Screenshot}}
<html>
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
	<style>

* {box-sizing: border-box;}
		.row {display: flex; flex: 50%;}

/* Createl columns that sits next to each other. Flex should be 100% divided by number of columns (2=50%, 3=33%, 4=25%) */
		.column1 {flex: 30%; width: 100%;}
		.column2 {flex: 70%; width: 100%;}
	</style>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="column1">
			<div id=ScreenshotFront>
				{{Screenshot}}
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="column2">
			<embed src="https://ichi.moe/cl/qr/?q={{Expression}}" style="width: 100%; height:100%; min-height: 400px; ">
		</div>
	</div>
</html>
{{/Screenshot}}

{{^Screenshot}}
	<embed src="https://ichi.moe/cl/qr/?q={{Expression}}" style="width: 100%; height:100%; min-height: 400px; ">
{{/Screenshot}}


{{#*}}-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
READ ME: These fields are hidden unless your mouse is over them.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------{{/*}}
<div class="Opacity">

<br>
	{{Tags}}
<br>
	{{ID}}
</div>

